{% extends 'index' %}

{% block 'main' %}

.hero-unit

  %h1 Installation for developers

  %br

  %p
    Wants to contribute or simply tweak the engine ? Here is the guide to run the engine

/ === 1 ===

%h3 1. prepare the environment on your machine

%br

%pre
  cd ~/Documents
  mkdir LocomotiveCMS
  cd LocomotiveCMS
  mkdir gems

%br

.alert.alert-info
  Replace the "~/Documents" folder by what you want.

%hr

/ === 2 ===

%h3 2. clone the engine and the core gems

%br

%pre
  cd gems
  git clone git://github.com/locomotivecms/custom_fields.git
  cd ..
  git clone git://github.com/locomotivecms/engine.git

%hr

/ === 3 ===

%h3 3. install the gems

%br

%pre
  cd engine
  bundle install

%hr

/ === 4 ===

%h3 4. run the application

%br

%pre
  cd spec/dummy
  bundle exec unicorn_rails

%hr

/ === 5 ===

%h3 5. run the test suite

%br 
  Caution: for all tests pass, you need
  %a{ :href => 'http://phantomjs.org'} PhantomJS 

.alert.alert-info
  If you have homebrew on your Mac OSx :
  %pre brew update && brew install phantomjs

%pre
  bundle exec rake

%p You can also run only the cucumber or rspec tests

%pre
  bundle exec rake cucumber
  bundle exec rake spec
  bundle exec rake rspec spec/models/locomotive/page_spec.rb

{% endblock %}